C(\lambda )\Omega (\alpha_2)-
D(\lambda )\Omega (\alpha_3)
\right\}=0
\]
and
\[
c_1\left\{
A(\lambda )\Theta (\alpha_1)-
B(\lambda )\Theta (\alpha_3)
\right\}
+
c_2\left\{
C(\lambda )\Theta (\alpha_2)-
D(\lambda )\Theta (\alpha_3)
\right\}=0\, ,
\]
where
\[
\Omega (\alpha ) = (1-\alpha )
{\left( \frac{\Lambda^2}{m^2}\right)}^{-\alpha}
\]
and
\[
\Theta (\alpha ) = \left[\alpha^2+(\lambda -1)\alpha +\lambda \right]
{\left( \frac{\Lambda^2}{m^2}\right)}^{-\alpha}\, .
\]
The coefficients are
\[
A(\lambda )=\prod_{i=1}^3\frac{\Gamma (\alpha_1+\gamma_i)}
{\Gamma (\alpha_1-\alpha_i+1)}
\]
\[
B(\lambda )=D(\lambda )=
\prod_{i=1}^3\frac{\Gamma (\alpha_3+\gamma_i)}
{\Gamma (\alpha_3-\alpha_i+1)}
\]
\[
C(\lambda )=\prod_{i=1}^3\frac{\Gamma (\alpha_2+\gamma_i)}
{\Gamma (\alpha_2-\alpha_i+1)}\, .
\]
Note that $u_c$ satisfies the simple formula
\[
u_c=\frac{-\lambda_c+\sqrt{\lambda_c^2-3\lambda_c+3}}{3}
\]
\[
v(\lambda )=\frac{\sqrt{3Q}}{A^2+AB+B^2}
\sim \mbox{\sf const} \sqrt{\lambda -\lambda_c}\, ,
\]
 Here we will not discuss further the influence of the
vacuum polarization effects on the dynamical mass function (see
the papers \cite{Kondo}).
